    "en": {
      "title": "A 'house in a row' for the houses that will be sold to the Kelaniweli railway line",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Transport, Highways and Mass Media Mr. Bandula Gunawardena observed the 'Malapalla' apartment project being built for the people who will lose their homes due to the Kelaniweli railway expansion project.",
        "For the project to modernize the Kelaniweli railway line into a double track, the Ministry of Transport has implemented a program to evacuate the illegal residents of the railway reserve from Maradana to Padukka and provide them with houses in other suitable places. Under this project, 120 new houses are being built in Kottawa - Malapalla area And so says the Ministry of Transport.",
        "The Ministry of Transport said that a house with two bedrooms, a living room, a kitchen, a bathroom and all facilities will be owned by a selected homeless family and it is planned to complete its construction in 2023.",
        "On that occasion, Railway General Manager W. that. B. S. e. P. A group of officials including Mr. Gunasinghe were present."
      ],
